casebody.data:
THE STATE OF FLORIDA v. JOHNNY DUNCAN alias TOMPKINS 23 So. (2nd) 855

June Term, 1945

November 27, 1945 Division A J. Tom, Watson, Attorney General, Beeves Bowen, Assistant Attorney General, Luther W. Cobbey, County Solicitor, and Paul Game, Assistant County Solicitor, for appellant. Joseph E. Williams and Gyrus W. Fields, for appellee. *585PER CURIAM:

Affirmed.

CHAPMAN, C. J., TERRELL, BROWN, THOMAS, ADAMS and SEBRING, JJ., concur. BUFORD, J., dissents. BUFORD, J.,

dissenting:

I think the information sufficiently charges a violation of Sec. 800.04, 1943 supplement to Vol. 1 Fla. Statutes 1941 and Sec. 794.05 Fla. Statutes 1941 and judgment should be reversed on authority of Eggart v. State 43 Fla. 527, 25 So. 144 in connection with Sec. 906.25 Fla. Statutes 1941.
